AFTER five years of pain and sufferingÂ  the family of Michael Komape will finally get closure. 'I FOUND HIM DEAD IN A TOILET' The 5-year-old drowned in a pit toilet at Mahlodumela Primary School, in Seshego, Limpopo, in January 2014. COURT DISMISSES DAMAGES CLAIM BY KOMAPE FAMILY! In April last year, the family lost its claim for general and constitutional damages for the death of their son. COURT CRUSHES KOMAPES! The Limpopo High Court in Polokwane then dismissed the claim Judge Gerrit Muller only ordered that two of Komape's siblings be paid R6 000 each for general medical expenses.  Section 27 appealed the judgment at the supreme court of appeal. KOMAPE FAMILY APPEAL GRANTED! Today the Supreme Court of Appeal gave judgment in the case against the order of the high court in which refused to award damages for emotional shock and grief. The Supreme Court of Appeal awarded damages of R1.4-million to Komape's family for his death. The Komapes were seeking R2-m in damages from the Basic Education Minister and the Limpopo Education MEC. Section 27 said it welcomes the judgment of the Supreme Court of Appeal (SCA). SECTION27 said it wishes to express its gratitude to Legal Aid South Africa for funding our representation of the Komape family and their pursuit for justice.  